'''Danny Berrios''' (born October 29, 1961) is an American [[Christian music]] singer-songwriter and [[televangelist]]. Son of [[Puerto Rican people|Puerto Rican]] preacher Jose Pepito Berrios and Clara Berrios.

==Background==
In 1980, Berríos begins his ministry, that same year makes its first presentation in Quetzaltenango (Guatemala) in a campaign that his father Pepito carried out. Since then he has performed hundreds of concerts and presentations live and has released numerous albums.

He has also ministered crusades along with evangelists and Christian leaders recognized internationally, as [[Luis Palau]], Alberto Motessi and [[Yiye Avila]]. He has also shared the stage with prestigious U.S. Christian preachers, among them [[Morris Cerullo]], [[Steve Fatow]], [[Billy Graham]], [[Larry Jones (pastor)|Larry Jones]], [[Larry Lea]] and [[Jimmy Swaggart]].

